Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt and @pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @Coriander{1%stalk}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).
Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).
Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion Shallot{1%large}(halved, peeled and chopped)
into small pieces.

Add the @Korma Curry Paste{50%g} into a #medium bowl{} and season with
@salt and @pepper.

Pat the @Sea Bass Fillets{2} with #kitchen paper{} to remove any excess moisture,
then add to the bowl. Use your hands to coat the fish well.

Lay on the korma sea bass fillets onto a lined baking tray, skin-side down.

Once the chips have been in the oven for ~{15%minutes}, pop the tray onto the
middle shelf and bake until the fish is cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked
> when opaque in the middle.

When the chips have ~{5%minutes} of cooking time left, melt the @Butter{20%g} in
a #small frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Stir in the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and
cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the @Peas{120%g}.

Stir-fry until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt and
@pepper.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix together the @Mango Chutney{40%g} and
@Mayonnaise{2%tbsp}.

When the peas are cooked, add half the coriander to the pan and stir through
until wilted.

When everything's ready, plate up the korma sea bass with the chips and peas
alongside.

Finish with a dollop of mango chutney mayo and a sprinkle of the remaining
coriander over the top.

Enjoy!